Dasineura crataegi, the hawthorn button-top gall-midge, is a dipteran gall-midge. It causes the hawthorn button-top gall, which develops in the terminal shoots of common hawthorn, Crataegus monogyna Jacq., Midland hawthorn C laevigata (Poir.) DC and their hybrid, C Ã— media Bechst.  Synonyms are Perrisia crataegi and Cecidomyia crataegi (Winnertz, 1853).